+{"id":"bd-jhb6","title":"Investigate post-write .beads SQLite instability after normal br commands","description":"Normal `br` write commands can transiently reintroduce tracker-health problems even after the canonical `.beads/beads.db` has been repaired and vacuumed.\n\nObserved behavior in this repo on 2026-04-07:\n- `br close` can mark `metadata.blocked_cache_state = stale`, which makes `br doctor` fail until the blocked cache is rebuilt.\n- `br ready` clears the stale blocked-cache marker but can reintroduce low-level `sqlite.integrity_check` warnings such as `page N is never used`.\n- A plain SQLite `VACUUM` on the canonical DB restores the clean end-state (`PRAGMA integrity_check = ok`, `page_count = 338`, `freelist_count = 0`).\n\nFollow-up work:\n1. Determine why these normal `br` writes leave the DB in a state that `integrity_check` reports as malformed in this workspace.\n2. Determine whether the issue is specific to the current beads DB image, frankensqlite/WAL behavior, or the current `br` version.\n3. Establish a durable workflow or upstream fix so agents do not need manual post-write vacuuming.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T16:32:02.679370681Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T16:32:02.679370681Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
